In [24]:
Q1 = df["SalePrice"].quantile(0.25)
Q3 = df["SalePrice"].quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
In [26]:
lower_bound = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR
upper_bound = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR
In [28]:
df = df[(df["SalePrice"] >= lower_bound) & (df["SalePrice"] <= upper_bound)]

In [36]:
for col in df.columns:
    if df[col].dtype in ["float64", "int64"]:
        median_val = df[col].median()
        df[col] = df[col].fillna(median_val)
    else:
        mode_val = df[col].mode()[0]
        df[col] = df[col].fillna(mode_val)

In [92]:
print("Jointplots: Top 10 by |corr| with SalePrice:")
for feature in top_by_abs:
    g = sns.jointplot(data=num_df, x=feature, y="SalePrice", kind="reg",
                      height=6, scatter_kws={"s":12, "alpha":0.5}, line_kws={"lw":2})
    g.fig.suptitle(f"Jointplot: {feature} vs SalePrice", y=1.02)
    plt.show()

6. انتخاب ویژگی‌ها با SelectKBest (روش f_regression)
In [100]:
from sklearn.feature_selection import SelectKBest, f_regression
In [102]:
from sklearn.preprocessing import OneHotEncoder
In [104]:
from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer
In [106]:
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline
In [108]:
from sklearn.linear_model import LinearRegression
In [110]:
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV, cross_val_score
In [112]:
import numpy as np
In [114]:
X = df.drop(columns=["SalePrice"])
y = df["SalePrice"]
In [116]:
cat_cols = X.select_dtypes(include=["object"]).columns.tolist()
num_cols = X.select_dtypes(exclude=["object"]).columns.tolist()
In [118]:
preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(
    transformers=[
        ("num", "passthrough", num_cols),
        ("cat", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown="ignore"), cat_cols),
    ]
)
In [120]:
pipe = Pipeline(steps=[
    ("preprocess", preprocessor),
    ("select", SelectKBest(score_func=f_regression, k=20)),  # k will be tuned
    ("model", LinearRegression())
])
In [122]:
param_grid = {"select__k": [5, 10, 20, 30, 40, 50]}
grid = GridSearchCV(
    pipe, param_grid=param_grid, scoring="r2", cv=5, n_jobs=-1, return_train_score=False
)
grid.fit(X, y)

In [190]:

    ("scaler", StandardScaler(with_mean=False)),

In [192]:

def rmse(y_true, y_pred):
    return np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))

In [235]:
def rmse(y_true, y_pred):
    return np.sqrt(mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred))
In [237]:
candidate_feats = ["Overall Qual","Gr Liv Area","Garage Cars","Year Built","Total Bsmt SF","1st Flr SF"]
num_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(exclude=["object"]).columns.tolist()
top_num_feats = [c for c in candidate_feats if c in num_cols]
assert len(top_num_feats) >= 4, "Not enough numeric features found from the candidate list."
In [239]:
degrees = [1, 2, 3, 4]
rows = []
In [241]:
for d in degrees:
    pre = ColumnTransformer(
        transformers=[
            ("num_poly", Pipeline([
                ("poly", PolynomialFeatures(degree=d, include_bias=False,
                                            interaction_only=(d >= 2))),
                ("scale", StandardScaler(with_mean=False))
            ]), top_num_feats),
        ],
        remainder="drop"
    )

    pipe = Pipeline(steps=[
        ("preprocess", pre),
        ("model", Ridge(alpha=1.0, random_state=42))
    ])

    pipe.fit(X_train, y_train)

    y_tr = pipe.predict(X_train)
    r2_tr = r2_score(y_train, y_tr)
    rmse_tr = rmse(y_train, y_tr)

    y_te = pipe.predict(X_test)
    r2_te = r2_score(y_test, y_te)
    rmse_te = rmse(y_test, y_te)

    rows.append({"Degree": d, "R2_train": r2_tr, "RMSE_train": rmse_tr,
                 "R2_test": r2_te, "RMSE_test": rmse_te})
In [243]:

    print("=== Polynomial degree vs performance (higher R2 better, lower RMSE better) ===")
    print(df_deg.to_string(index=False))
